<center>
<font size = "3"><b>Library to end Sunday openings</font></b><br>
February 29, 2016<p></center>


The Penticton Public Library Board of Directors has voted unanimously to end the Librarys Sunday open hours effective immediately in the face of static funding expectations in 2016. Library Board Chair, Linda King, says: We strive to provide the best possible service to our community, and while we regret this decision, increasing costs require us to shift resources, investing in key areas to improve our services overall. <p>

The decision was made over options which included reducing the book acquisitions budget which has been held at the same level since before 2012. These include print and e-books, both of which are seeing an increase in price in 2016. Other areas the library considered for cuts include planned upgrades to the public computers and website. 

<p>
